   =20
      Ronin
   =20
 =20
Axie Infinity is an online world where people toil in indentured servitude =
to earn cryptocurrency for =E2=80=9Csponsors=E2=80=9D who take as much as 9=
0% of their earnings, but on the blockchain. Also I guess it is a video gam=
e. I  once wrote about it:Doesn=E2=80=99t it feel like the dystopian future=
 we deserve? Like in a decade everyone will make their living by steering c=
olorful blob-like creatures around to acquire coins in a virtual world, but=
 ownership of the colorful blob-like virtual creatures will be concentrated=
 among a hereditary elite of people who, like, bought Dogecoin in 2014, and=
 in order to scrape together enough to live on you will need to indenture y=
ourself to a member of that elite, steering their blob-like virtual creatur=
es around to earn coins for them and getting a few crumbs for yourself. And=
 you=E2=80=99ll work 16-hour days in the Smooth Love Potions mines just to =
feed your children, but every once in a while in a rare free moment you wil=
l stop and ask yourself =E2=80=9Cwait why do our overlords want all these S=
mooth Love Potions anyway?=E2=80=9DMeanwhile the overlords will form a leis=
ure class and devote themselves to philosophy and philanthropy. They=E2=80=
=99ll keep busy collecting non-fungible-token art and putting their names o=
n virtual library buildings in the metaverse and writing manifestos about h=
ow cryptocurrency enhances human freedom and levels the playing field for e=
veryone.Anyway, good news,  hackers stole its cryptocurrency:Hackers stole =
about $600 million from a blockchain network connected to the popular Axie =
Infinity online game in one of the biggest crypto attacks to date.Computers=
 known as nodes operated by Axie Infinity maker Sky Mavis and the Axie DAO =
that support a so-called bridge -- software that lets people convert tokens=
 into ones that can be used on another network -- were attacked, with the h=
acker draining what=E2=80=99s known as the Ronin Bridge of 173,600 Ether an=
d 25.5 million USDC tokens in two transactions. The breach happened on Marc=
h 23, but was only discovered Tuesday, according to=C2=A0Ronin, the blockch=
ain that supports Axie Infinity.Here is Ronin=E2=80=99s explanation of the =
hack, which is basically =E2=80=9Cwe had secure validation procedures, but =
they took too long, so we built a shortcut when things got busy, and then w=
e forgot to turn off the shortcut.=E2=80=9D Nobody cares less about informa=
tion security than the builders of cryptocurrency projects.
