      Goldman
   =20
 =20
=E2=80=9CJunior bankers at Goldman Sachs are threatening to quit over deman=
ds that they show up to the office five days a week,=E2=80=9D it says here,=
 and I feel inconceivably old. Disclosure! I worked at Goldman =E2=80=94 I =
left=C2=A010 (!)=C2=A0years ago =E2=80=94=C2=A0and if you had told me then=
=C2=A0that one day JUNIOR BANKERS AT GOLDMAN SACHS WOULD COMPLAIN ABOUT SHO=
WING UP TO THE OFFICE FIVE DAYS A WEEK I simply would not have believed you=
. =E2=80=9CJunior bankers at Goldman Sachs are threatening to quit over dem=
ands that they show up to the office seven days a week,=E2=80=9D maybe, if =
it was=C2=A0every=C2=A0week, but five? In investment banking? Nothing says =
=E2=80=9CCovid-19 has permanently changed the world of work=E2=80=9D like =
=E2=80=9CJunior bankers at Goldman Sachs are threatening to quit over deman=
ds that they show up to the office five days a week.=E2=80=9D Five!I=E2=80=
=99m sure it=E2=80=99s unpleasant but still:As bonuses across Wall Street h=
it record highs, underlings at Goldman =E2=80=94 headed by hard-charging Ch=
ief Executive David Solomon =E2=80=94 are nevertheless stepping up complain=
ts of =E2=80=9Chellhole=E2=80=9D working conditions that have notoriously i=
ncluded 100-hour weeks.Most recently, some junior Goldmanites claim that th=
ey are being =E2=80=9Cbullied=E2=80=9D into showing up in person =E2=80=9C5=
-0=E2=80=9D =E2=80=94 meaning five days working in the office, zero from ho=
me =E2=80=94 and that the bullying is being orchestrated by top managers ar=
med with spreadsheets.=E2=80=9CIn GS, the top management says it=E2=80=99s =
employees choice but internally they track which team has most in office at=
tendance,=E2=80=9D one Goldman employee wrote on the corporate message boar=
d Blind, which verifies users=E2=80=99 place of employment with the help of=
 their company email accounts. =E2=80=A6A Goldman spokesperson declined to =
comment for the record. A person close to the bank disputed there was wides=
pread frustration. =E2=80=9CFar from a scientific survey, The Post has chos=
en a handful of comments submitted to an online forum no one has heard of.=
=E2=80=9DProbably some of them would like to come in to the office less oft=
en, sure. But they work at Goldman!=C2=A0
