      Things happen
   =20
 =20
From VW to JPMorgan, the Unlikely Cast Behind  Nickel=E2=80=99s Big Squeeze=
.=C2=A0Icahn  Blasts Kroger for Low Wages, =E2=80=98Torturous=E2=80=99 Pig =
Crates. Hedge Funds That Took  Roman Abramovich=E2=80=99s Billions Have No =
Way Out. Germany Braces for Less Gas as Russia Demands Ruble Payments. Bank=
ers Are Still Standing Behind the  Dirtiest Fossil Fuel.  Chicken Price-Fix=
ing Prosecution Ends in Second Mistrial.=C2=A0Bombardier Hires Cravath, See=
ks to Dismiss  Bond Default Lawsuit. People are worried about  duration. =
=E2=80=9C=E2=80=98When you invest in China, there=E2=80=99s  no point for d=
ocuments,=E2=80=99 Lim said. =E2=80=98Even if I have a document, where do I=
 go to enforce it?=E2=80=99=E2=80=9D=C2=A0California man caught with dozens=
 of lizards in his clothes is charged with smuggling 1,700 reptiles.=C2=A0I=
f you'd like to get=C2=A0Money=C2=A0Stuff=C2=A0in handy email form, right i=
n your inbox, please=C2=A0subscribe at this link. Or you can subscribe to M=
oney Stuff and other great Bloomberg newsletters here. Thanks![1] There are=
 also dark pools =E2=80=94=C2=A0ECNs, for =E2=80=9Celectronic communication=
s network=E2=80=9D =E2=80=94=C2=A0that keep later hours than the exchanges.=
[2] Another way to read it is: =E2=80=9CRobinhood=E2=80=99s shareholders, w=
ho are often also its customers, are pretty meme-focused, and the fact that=
 this sounds good to them is enough to push up the stock even though every =
other retail broker already does it.=E2=80=9D[3] See Rule 611, and the defi=
nition of =E2=80=9Ctrade-through=E2=80=9D in Rule 600(b)(94).[4] Not just b=
ecause there is less competition among market makers, by the way. There is =
also a higher risk of adverse selection: If someone is trading after hours,=
 and dealing with the illiquidity and wide spreads, it is probably because =
they are particularly axed to trade. Perhaps they have a lot of stock to se=
ll, which will move the price, or perhaps they know something about the sto=
ck that is not yet reflected in the price. (After all, a lot of news comes =
out before the open or after the close, meaning you can trade on it in the =
extended session.) This is all bad for market makers: There=E2=80=99s more =
risk of adverse selection in the extended session. So they need to charge w=
ider spreads.
